Dude, Nomad is not here.

235
00:19:59,999 --> 00:20:02,067
- Let's take a look.
- He's not here.

236
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:04,769
We'll take a look
and then we'll go.

237
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,071
Let's go find him.

238
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:09,506
A hillbilly lives here.

239
00:20:11,108 --> 00:20:14,010
- This guy has a baby?
- Shh!

240
00:20:18,916 --> 00:20:20,349
Shh!

241
00:20:48,447 --> 00:20:50,213
Jonah?

242
00:20:53,285 --> 00:20:54,984
Jonah?

243
00:21:04,328 --> 00:21:06,096
Jonah?

244
00:21:07,065 --> 00:21:09,534
Dude, I can see you.
What are you doing?

245
00:21:09,535 --> 00:21:11,201
Hey!

246
00:21:17,576 --> 00:21:20,143
Dude, you're such an asshole!

247
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:24,383
How funny is this little chair?

248
00:21:24,384 --> 00:21:26,917
It was really facing
the corner like this.

249
00:21:26,919 --> 00:21:29,419
Come on. There's a basement.

250
00:21:30,923 --> 00:21:33,556
You're such a kike.

251
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:40,763
- Go down.
- Screw that, you go down.

252
00:21:42,768 --> 00:21:44,534
Be careful.

253
00:21:57,182 --> 00:21:59,415
What is this place?

254
00:22:02,186 --> 00:22:04,320
Check it out, man.

255
00:22:07,459 --> 00:22:09,459
What are those?

256
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:13,163
- Server racks.
- That's weird.

257
00:22:20,238 --> 00:22:22,271
Oh, wait. Haley!

258
00:22:23,575 --> 00:22:26,676
Haley! Haley! Haley!

259
00:22:28,813 --> 00:22:30,779
Haley!

260
00:22:36,121 --> 00:22:37,655
What the hell?

261
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:40,592
- What was that sound?
- I don't know.

262
00:22:40,593 --> 00:22:43,961
- Why are the car doors open like that?
- I don't know!

263
00:22:43,962 --> 00:22:45,729
Haley!

264
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:55,672
- Haley!
- Shh!

265
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:57,906
Listen.

266
00:23:06,451 --> 00:23:07,751
Oh, my God.

267
00:23:08,988 --> 00:23:11,221
- Haley!
- Haley!

268
00:23:11,589 --> 00:23:13,556
Haley!

269
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:58,861
Can you... speak?

270
00:25:00,131 --> 00:25:02,465
Where am I?

271
00:25:03,734 --> 00:25:05,868
I can't move.

272
00:25:07,404 --> 00:25:09,505
Can you tell me your name?

273
00:25:10,875 --> 00:25:13,211
Nicholas Eastman.

274
00:25:13,211 --> 00:25:15,579
I'm Damon. Dr. Wallace Damon.

275
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:20,050
I'm heading up the transition
team that's going to help you,

276
00:25:20,051 --> 00:25:25,989
help all of us understand exactly
what you've been through.

277
00:25:26,458 --> 00:25:29,192
What are you talking about?

278
00:25:30,394 --> 00:25:34,798
Can you recall for me the first
time you encountered the signal?

279
00:25:35,066 --> 00:25:36,967
The what?

280
00:25:39,336 --> 00:25:41,637
Why can't I move?

281
00:25:42,773 --> 00:25:44,342
What happened to us?

282
00:25:44,343 --> 00:25:47,578
Due to the circumstances
surrounding your condition,

283
00:25:47,579 --> 00:25:53,115
I'm afraid that our information
is... extremely limited.

284
00:25:53,183 --> 00:25:55,787
Wait, what's my condition?

285
00:25:55,788 --> 00:26:00,189
What I'm about to tell you, Nic,
you may find a bit disturbing.

286
00:26:00,858 --> 00:26:04,760
You have made contact
with an E.B.E.

287
00:26:05,363 --> 00:26:07,265
E.B.E.?

288
00:26:07,266 --> 00:26:12,201
Extraterrestrial Biological
Entity. E.B.E.

289
00:26:14,873 --> 00:26:17,473
I want to talk to my parents.

290
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:23,948
- I'm sorry, that's just not possible.
- What are you talking about?

291
00:26:23,949 --> 00:26:28,919
Where's Haley and Jonah?
What happened to us?

292
00:26:29,988 --> 00:26:33,423
Why am I... in a wheelchair?

293
00:26:38,128 --> 00:26:40,330
Why...

294
00:26:40,332 --> 00:26:42,632
Why are you wearing that suit?

295
00:26:44,368 --> 00:26:48,906
We're not 100% certain about
what we're dealing with here.

296
00:26:48,907 --> 00:26:53,478
The possibility for alien
contamination is... very real.

297
00:26:53,479 --> 00:26:56,112
When you say "alien
contamination," do you mean...

298
00:26:56,114 --> 00:27:00,040
microbiological
contamination, as in foreign?

299
00:27:00,218 --> 00:27:02,085
Hold still.

300
00:27:19,738 --> 00:27:21,238
Oh.

301
00:27:24,843 --> 00:27:26,910
It's just blood.

302
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:31,113
<i>It's just blood.</i>

303
00:27:33,417 --> 00:27:36,419
I think we'll stop here for today.

304
00:28:48,092 --> 00:28:51,784
<i>Contact values at 9, 8,</i>

305
00:28:51,785 --> 00:28:56,031
<i>47, 91, 72.</i>

306
00:29:01,538 --> 00:29:04,707
<i>Level 12. Do we know current value?</i>

307
00:29:39,076 --> 00:29:43,090
Stop! Will you stop? Stop!

308
00:29:43,092 --> 00:29:46,648
Go back! Can you go back?

309
00:29:56,361 --> 00:29:58,627
What's wrong with Haley?

310
00:30:01,164 --> 00:30:04,368
As advanced as we are,

311
00:30:04,369 --> 00:30:10,972
it's amazing that a tool as crude
as a pen still has its place.

312
00:30:13,111 --> 00:30:15,310
There we go.

313
00:30:16,446 --> 00:30:20,650
I want to talk to Haley. Please.

314
00:30:21,519 --> 00:30:24,119
I'm afraid that's not
possible right now.

315
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:25,690
Why?

316
00:30:25,691 --> 00:30:27,992
She's in good hands,
Nic, I promise you.

317
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:30,961
The best thing you can do for
her right now is to help us.

318
00:30:30,962 --> 00:30:34,697
Now, will you please try
to cooperate with me?

319
00:30:38,536 --> 00:30:40,869
- Okay.
- Good.

320
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:47,042
First I'm going to ask you
some simple control questions.

321
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:51,012
Do you have 10 toes?

322
00:30:55,953 --> 00:30:57,854
Yes.

323
00:31:00,991 --> 00:31:03,692
Are you from Earth?

324
00:31:08,432 --> 00:31:12,701
- Yes, I am from Earth.
- Good, thank you.

325
00:31:13,904 --> 00:31:16,507
Now, this signal that you and
your friends were pursuing,

326
00:31:16,508 --> 00:31:18,108
when did you first encounter it?

327
00:31:18,109 --> 00:31:20,743
- You mean Nomad.
- Yes.

328
00:31:20,744 --> 00:31:23,779
MIT. He got into our
school's security network

329
00:31:23,786 --> 00:31:27,883
and ruined some major servers,
including our personal ones.

330
00:31:33,191 --> 00:31:36,192
Nic, I want you to watch something.

331
00:31:47,873 --> 00:31:50,539
<i>A big mama sat in that chair.</i>

332
00:32:18,536 --> 00:32:21,703
You definitely weren't
pursuing a hacker.

333
00:32:44,228 --> 00:32:46,061
Hey.

334
00:32:51,035 --> 00:32:52,902
Hey.

335
00:32:54,372 --> 00:32:57,873
- Jonah?
- Nic.

336
00:32:57,909 --> 00:33:01,175
- Jonah!
- Nic!

337
00:33:01,612 --> 00:33:03,280
Oh, my God! Jonah, where are you?

338
00:33:03,281 --> 00:33:06,517
I don't know. I'm locked
up, I'm in a room.

339
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:10,253
Me, too. I'm in a locked room,
dude. Where are we?

340
00:33:10,255 --> 00:33:14,392
I heard them say we're not allowed above
ground because we were contaminated.

341
00:33:14,393 --> 00:33:17,327
What the hell was Nomad?
What have they told you?

342
00:33:17,328 --> 00:33:19,230
Not much.

343
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:23,300
I saw Haley. She's in
a coma or something.

344
00:33:23,301 --> 00:33:27,502
Nic, they're doing some
weird shit here, man.

345
00:33:27,538 --> 00:33:30,272
My body doesn't feel right.

346
00:33:30,942 --> 00:33:34,112
- Nic, I gotta go.
- What? Where?

347
00:33:34,113 --> 00:33:38,548
This place is run like a clock.
I can't believe you're in the vent!

348
00:33:38,549 --> 00:33:40,718
What? Dude, I'm not in the vent.

349
00:33:40,719 --> 00:33:44,788
I'm not in the vent! Jonah! Jonah!

350
00:33:48,792 --> 00:33:52,762
- Why don't you have any clocks that work?
- Clocks that work?

351
00:33:52,763 --> 00:33:54,598
Yeah. The one in the
hallway is stuck at 12:30.

352
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:57,434
- Which hallway?
- Seven windows back. Left turn.

353
00:33:57,435 --> 00:33:59,202
Four windows. Right turn.
Two windows on the right.

354
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:03,301
Next to the bathroom with its sign
upside down. It's stuck at 12:30.

355
00:34:03,305 --> 00:34:09,246
Nic, it's a broken clock. Thank you
for bringing it to my attention.

356
00:34:09,248 --> 00:34:13,581
Can we please proceed with
the shapes and colors?

357
00:34:13,617 --> 00:34:17,059
- Screw this. This is stupid.
- What's the matter, Nic?

358
00:34:17,059 --> 00:34:19,422
- Can't you do it?
- No, I choose not to do it.

359
00:34:19,423 --> 00:34:24,461
Choose? You choose not to do it?
That sounds like pride talking.

360
00:34:24,463 --> 00:34:27,563
False and foolish pride. That's all.

361
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:36,873
Pyramid, yellow.

362
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:39,976
- And the...
- Cube, blue. Sphere, green.

363
00:34:39,978 --> 00:34:42,681
The blue tile here that says "Zero"
corresponds with the green cube.

364
00:34:42,681 --> 00:34:44,782
The yellow tile here that says
"Six" goes with the cube.

365
00:34:44,782 --> 00:34:47,318
The green tile here that says "Five"
goes with the yellow pyramid.

366
00:34:47,318 --> 00:34:49,420
The green cube goes with
the blue shaped cube.

367
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:51,255
The yellow written sphere goes
with the green-shaped sphere.

368
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:53,391
The blue written pyramid goes
with the yellow-shaped pyramid.

369
00:34:53,391 --> 00:34:55,025
"Blue," written in yellow,
"yellow," in green,

370
00:34:55,027 --> 00:34:57,094
correspond the visible colors and
shapes rather than the written words

371
00:34:57,096 --> 00:34:59,963
because the spectral quality of light
is more objective, so to speak,

372
00:34:59,965 --> 00:35:03,032
than the written English
words of those colors.

373
00:35:04,668 --> 00:35:07,905
- I see.
- You see? What do you mean, you see?

374
00:35:07,905 --> 00:35:10,240
You, Nic.

375
00:35:10,242 --> 00:35:14,010
I see you and I think I'm beginning to
understand something more about you.

376
00:35:14,012 --> 00:35:16,079
Understand what?

377
00:35:17,047 --> 00:35:19,751
The colors, the shapes,
they have an effect on you.

378
00:35:19,751 --> 00:35:22,018
I'd say it was an emotional
effect, wouldn't you?

379
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:24,644
I don't care about the shapes and
colors, they don't mean anything to me.

380
00:35:24,646 --> 00:35:28,590
They don't mean shit to me! You're the
one that's infuriating me, you quack!

381
00:35:29,693 --> 00:35:31,561
"Quack."

382
00:35:32,096 --> 00:35:33,730
"Quack."

383
00:35:34,264 --> 00:35:37,302
I wanna see Haley

384
00:35:37,503 --> 00:35:41,103
and I'm not gonna say another
word until you let me see her.

385
00:35:43,373 --> 00:35:45,641
Okay, Nic.

386
00:35:54,251 --> 00:35:55,885
There's nothing on here.

387
00:35:55,887 --> 00:35:59,420
She's in a coma, Nic.

388
00:35:59,523 --> 00:36:03,159
There's nothing that can
be done for her right now.

389
00:36:03,927 --> 00:36:08,032
I promise, as soon as she wakes up,
you'll be the first one to see her.

390
00:36:08,032 --> 00:36:11,601
Right now we're doing
everything humanly possible.

391
00:36:50,407 --> 00:36:52,809
<i>Nic, this place is insane.</i>

392
00:36:52,811 --> 00:36:55,246
Yeah, I know. Listen.
You were right.

393
00:36:55,246 --> 00:36:59,083
This place is run like a clock.
Listen, I need your help.

394
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:00,918
I've been keeping some
event sequences...

395
00:37:00,918 --> 00:37:04,021
Nic, it was hard to put
all this together,

396
00:37:04,021 --> 00:37:07,257
but, you know, I think
we're sick, or infected.

397
00:37:07,259 --> 00:37:10,193
Hey, Jonah, stop thinking
like that, man. Seriously.

398
00:37:10,195 --> 00:37:13,264
No, they're trying to keep whatever's
inside us from metastasizing.

399
00:37:13,264 --> 00:37:16,766
Jonah, stop. Nothing's
metastasizing, okay?

400
00:37:16,768 --> 00:37:18,635
- We're fine. We're gonna be fine.
- No, I'm not.

401
00:37:18,637 --> 00:37:21,503
- Just trust me on this.
- No, my body is not.

402
00:37:22,606 --> 00:37:24,940
We gotta get out of here.

403
00:37:25,608 --> 00:37:28,179
Yeah, I know. We will.

404
00:37:28,179 --> 00:37:30,481
Okay, I've got the
variables on my keypad.

405
00:37:30,481 --> 00:37:33,150
Now I need you to take back
half the sequences, okay?

406
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:35,619
- Yeah. I'll help.
- Okay.

407
00:37:35,619 --> 00:37:39,990
- But my glasses are messed up, though.
- Hey, it's gonna be fine.

408
00:37:39,992 --> 00:37:43,626
It's gonna be fine. Don't
worry about your glasses.

409
00:37:43,628 --> 00:37:45,061
Okay, I'm gonna give
it to you spatially.

410
00:37:45,063 --> 00:37:47,797
Three v three phone style.
Okay, you ready?

411
00:37:47,797 --> 00:37:50,233
- Yeah.
- Okay.

412
00:37:50,235 --> 00:37:56,005
Top-middle, middle-middle,
top-left, bottom-left.

413
00:37:56,005 --> 00:37:58,976
- 2-5-1-7.
- You got it?

414
00:37:58,976 --> 00:38:00,844
Bottom-left first.

415
00:38:00,846 --> 00:38:05,581
Middle-middle second.
Top-middle third.

416
00:38:06,050 --> 00:38:08,449
Top-left last.

417
00:38:11,588 --> 00:38:14,592
Nic, I'm having a hard
time handling this.

418
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:17,728
They made me drink some
weird stuff the other day

419
00:38:17,728 --> 00:38:21,096
and I haven't really been
able to feel my arms.

420
00:38:22,365 --> 00:38:26,534
Your arms? What? What do you mean?

421
00:38:26,536 --> 00:38:28,505
Oh, God!

422
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:34,177
- Dude, who is it?
- I gotta go.

423
00:38:34,179 --> 00:38:36,679
Jonah, hold on a second.

424
00:38:37,715 --> 00:38:41,016
Jonah! Jonah!

425
00:38:41,518 --> 00:38:43,351
Jonah!

426
00:39:13,483 --> 00:39:15,650
Agitate.

427
00:39:46,451 --> 00:39:48,416
<i>Everybody outside.</i>

428
00:39:49,186 --> 00:39:53,523
<i>Recovery team to level 14.
Subject has breached.</i>

429
00:39:53,525 --> 00:39:55,824
<i>Subject has escaped.</i>

430
00:40:09,106 --> 00:40:12,643
Oh, sorry, I was just looking
for the water fountain.

431
00:40:25,523 --> 00:40:28,190
<i>Recovery team to level 14.</i>

432
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:32,427
<i>Subject has breached. Escaped.</i>

433
00:40:52,983 --> 00:40:55,452
<i>Can you raise your arm?</i>

434
00:40:55,454 --> 00:40:57,918
<i>What happened in the hallway?</i>

435
00:41:03,860 --> 00:41:05,760
Good.

436
00:41:05,996 --> 00:41:08,264
Still no feeling in your legs?

437
00:41:08,266 --> 00:41:11,101
What happened to Jonah?

438
00:41:11,603 --> 00:41:14,672
Look, I know you guys know I
can talk to him through the vent.

439
00:41:14,672 --> 00:41:16,340
What the hell did you
guys do with him?

440
00:41:16,340 --> 00:41:18,842
Yes, Nic, we have been
listening to you,

441
00:41:18,842 --> 00:41:21,471
- but the truth of the matter...
- The truth of the matter is,

442
00:41:21,472 --> 00:41:23,246
total Mickey Mouse operation here.

443
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:26,983
Antiquated methodologies,
dinosaurs with government grants.

444
00:41:26,985 --> 00:41:29,619
A whole facility built during
the first wave of Big Science

445
00:41:29,621 --> 00:41:33,356
outdated but allowed to continue
pretending that you're important.

446
00:41:33,358 --> 00:41:35,525
- I feel sorry for you. It's pathetic.
- Nic.

447
00:41:35,527 --> 00:41:38,159
"The truth of the matter."

448
00:41:38,528 --> 00:41:40,630
What is the truth
of the matter here?

449
00:41:40,632 --> 00:41:44,034
The only thing I know for certain is that
you don't know what you're dealing with.

450
00:41:44,034 --> 00:41:47,605
You will be pulled from this shitty little
shack you call a research facility so fast

451
00:41:47,606 --> 00:41:49,773
that the only thing relevant
to be shown for any of this

452
00:41:49,773 --> 00:41:51,842
is the way it's all exposed,
wrecked, and forgotten.

453
00:41:51,842 --> 00:41:54,844
You have no idea!
You have no clue! Do you?

454
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:57,440
Have any clue how fast dumb,
lost little kids like me,

455
00:41:57,442 --> 00:41:59,525
Jonah or Nomad could
ruin a place like this?

456
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:02,219
Have it come to a grinding halt
like the stone wheel it is?

457
00:42:02,219 --> 00:42:04,188
You're clueless law in
the Wild West, Damon.

458
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:08,257
You're a relic protecting
ruins. You're pathetic.

459
00:42:08,259 --> 00:42:12,262
The truth of the matter is, I'm the
only one with any sense around here.

460
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,367
Your friend Jonah...

461
00:42:20,637 --> 00:42:21,972
was never here, Nic.

462
00:42:21,972 --> 00:42:25,773
- We never recovered him.
- Bullshit!

463
00:42:26,076 --> 00:42:28,846
I've been talking to him through
the vent this whole time.

464
00:42:28,847 --> 00:42:31,012
Have you really?

465
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:35,317
Through your vent, Nic?

466
00:43:50,527 --> 00:43:55,063
Three, four, five, six, seven...

467
00:44:07,844 --> 00:44:10,077
Shit.

468
00:44:58,661 --> 00:45:00,795
Shit!

469
00:45:15,278 --> 00:45:17,012
God damn it!

470
00:46:56,445 --> 00:46:58,746
Nic.

471
00:47:06,889 --> 00:47:08,990
Hey.

472
00:47:10,960 --> 00:47:13,293
How are you feeling?

473
00:47:13,963 --> 00:47:16,331
Better.

474
00:47:40,958 --> 00:47:43,891
I had a wonderful dream.

475
00:47:44,226 --> 00:47:46,728
Oh, yeah?

476
00:47:47,230 --> 00:47:49,630
You, um...

477
00:47:50,833 --> 00:47:53,034
You...

478
00:47:54,771 --> 00:47:58,005
You won your regionals.

479
00:48:03,447 --> 00:48:07,416
Hay, wake up. Wake up.

480
00:48:07,416 --> 00:48:09,583
Haley.

481
